#: ../../../getting_started.rst:-1
msgid ""
"A beginner's guide to Spack, walking you through the initial setup, basic "
"commands, and core concepts to get you started with managing software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:13
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:15
msgid ""
"Getting Spack is easy. You can clone it from the `GitHub repository <https://"
"github.com/spack/spack>`_ using this command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:18
msgid "$ git clone --depth=2 https://github.com/spack/spack.git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:22
msgid ""
"This will create a directory called ``spack``. Once you have cloned Spack, "
"we recommend sourcing the appropriate script for your shell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:25
msgid "For *bash*, *zsh* and *sh* users:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:27
msgid "$ . spack/share/spack/setup-env.sh"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:31
msgid "For *csh* and *tcsh* users:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:33
msgid "$ source spack/share/spack/setup-env.csh"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:37
msgid "For *fish* users:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:39
msgid "$ . spack/share/spack/setup-env.fish"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:43
msgid "Now you're ready to use Spack!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:46
msgid "List packages you can install"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:48
msgid ""
"Once Spack is ready, you can list all the packages it knows about with the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:50
msgid "$ spack list"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:54
msgid ""
"If you want to get more information on a specific package, for instance "
"``hdf5``, you can use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:56
msgid "$ spack info hdf5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:60
msgid ""
"This command shows information about ``hdf5``, including a brief "
"description, the versions of the package Spack knows about, and all the "
"options you can activate when installing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:62
msgid ""
"As you can see, it's quite simple to gather basic information on packages "
"before you install them!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:64
msgid "Slowdown on the very first command"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:67
msgid ""
"The first command you run with Spack may take a while, as Spack builds "
"caches to speed up future commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:70
msgid "Installing your first package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:72
msgid ""
"To install most packages, Spack needs a compiler suite to be available. To "
"search your machine for available compilers, you can run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:75
msgid "$ spack compiler find"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:79
msgid ""
"The command shows users whether any compilers were found and where their "
"configuration is stored. If the search was successful, you can now list "
"known compilers, and get an output similar to the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:82
msgid ""
"$ spack compiler list\n"
"==> Available compilers\n"
"-- gcc ubuntu20.04-x86_64 ---------------------------------------\n"
"[e]  gcc@9.4.0  [e]  gcc@8.4.0  [e]  gcc@10.5.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:89
msgid "If no compilers were found, you need to either:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:91
msgid ""
"Install further prerequisites, see :ref:`verify-spack-prerequisites`, and "
"repeat the search above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:92
msgid ""
"Register a buildcache that provides a compiler already available as a binary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:94
msgid ""
"Once a compiler is available, you can proceed installing your first package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.rst:96
msgid "$ spack install tcl"
msgstr ""

